# About Me
## Who I Am
I am Joshua Camacho, a senior at Corner Canyon Highschool, currently enrolled it the Computer Programming and New & Emerging classes at CTEC. I never full understood how AI worked or why people are so invested in making AI, but as my interest in learning how to program to try and make my own game some day, I became curious about AI. I decided to take this class to try to understand how AI works and possible try and harness as I try to understand the true career path I want to go into.


I want to show how AI can be used on a broader terms and not confined to some singular idea.
Key Focus Areas:
- Harnessing AI in such a way to help orientate story tell for a game.
- Coding and prompting an AI effectively as I try to tell a story through a game.
- I am already decent at making good prompts that help guide AI to produce what I want.
## What Drives Me
I have love playing games that bring both fast paced action and a story to life. I also enjoyed reading books like "The Way of Kings" by Brandon Sanderson. During my senior year, I joined a club that plays Dungeons and Dragons, a role playing game that combines a game of chance and maybe skill with story telling.
This porfolio will contain all of my AI codes and prompts that I will engineer throughout this cource a beyond.
My Approach:
When I did the Prompt Engineering project I feel into my usual pit fall of over thinking and never being able to rap my head around one thought or idea when making anything or even coding. But as I kept trying to engineer my first prompt I remember back to the few times I had used AI for somethings and realized I had some kind of pattern of what I wanted the AI to give me and I took that and reversed engineered it by adding placeholders of what I would usual ask which stand as the parameters. Doing this not only made it easier to engineer a prompt, but it help me figure out how to fix the prompt when it fails.
